1
00:00:01,020 --> 00:00:04,370
<i>[A Story to Read When You First Fall in Love]</i>

2
00:00:04,370 --> 00:00:06,090
<i>It's hard...</i>

3
00:00:06,090 --> 00:00:08,660
<i>when the woman I love is by my side the whole time.</i>

4
00:00:08,660 --> 00:00:10,940
<i>You can't do anything until your 18th birthday!</i>

5
00:00:10,940 --> 00:00:12,990
<i>Now I know why Yuri-zo was acting weird.</i>

6
00:00:12,990 --> 00:00:15,420
<i>I don't know if you're playing a penalty game or what,</i>

7
00:00:15,420 --> 00:00:17,740
<i>but we're busy, so cut it out!</i>

8
00:00:17,740 --> 00:00:20,200
<i>If I have a romantic relationship with my student,</i>

9
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,380
<i>I'll have to give up being your teacher.</i>

10
00:00:22,380 --> 00:00:24,700
<i>I absolutely want to be by your side</i>

11
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,620
<i> when you pass the exam.</i>

12
00:00:26,620 --> 00:00:28,660
<i>Are you okay?</i>

13
00:00:30,060 --> 00:00:39,960
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by
</i>ðŸ’–True Love TeamðŸ’–<i>@Viki.com</i>

14
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:47,420
Gosh, my head hurts.

15
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:51,960
<i>What on earth is she doing?</i>

16
00:00:53,950 --> 00:00:58,190
<i>How did I end up like this in the first place?</i>

17
00:00:58,190 --> 00:00:59,900
<i>Why...?</i>

18
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,320
<i>[June 4th, 2018]</i>

19
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:11,930
<i>Right...
[April 19th, 2018]</i>

20
00:01:11,930 --> 00:01:14,480
<i>- That's right. I remember now.</i>
- I envy

21
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:19,250
those who happily married in young age.

22
00:01:21,420 --> 00:01:23,630
What's happiness, anyway?

23
00:01:23,630 --> 00:01:25,870
You don't think about what happiness is

24
00:01:25,870 --> 00:01:28,540
when you're living a happy life.

25
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:30,580
Indeed.

26
00:01:34,450 --> 00:01:36,130
<i>[Yuka]</i>

27
00:01:36,710 --> 00:01:41,300
<i>I know that because I've come to realize that I'm not happy.</i>

28
00:01:45,670 --> 00:01:47,460
Hello?

29
00:01:48,540 --> 00:01:51,390
<i>Kazuma? Where are you right now? </i>

30
00:01:52,190 --> 00:01:54,550
I'm out drinking now.

31
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:58,610
<i>You should've told me. If you forget next time, I'll divorce you.</i>

32
00:01:58,610 --> 00:02:01,640
Sorry. I'll be home soon.

33
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:07,570
Plans for the Golden Week?

34
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:09,890
I'm attending the study camp for the cram school.

35
00:02:09,890 --> 00:02:13,850
- It's a good opportunity to tutor Yuri-yuri all day long.
<i>- No, that's not it.</i>

36
00:02:13,850 --> 00:02:16,860
<i>I hadn't realized it yet then.</i>

37
00:02:17,790 --> 00:02:19,590
<i>The only answer is...</i>

38
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:21,040
<i>[April 19th, 2018]</i>

39
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:23,610
<i>[May 5th, 2018]</i>

40
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:25,740
<i>[Divorce Registration Form, Yuka Yamashita]</i>

41
00:02:41,890 --> 00:02:45,870
<i>Hey! This is not the time to be depressed.</i>

42
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:47,250
<i>[June 4th, 2018]</i>

43
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:50,420
Anyway, somehow...

44
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,710
I have to get rid of this!

45
00:02:53,650 --> 00:02:55,650
All right!

46
00:02:55,650 --> 00:03:00,230
<i>Because I'll be wrapped up like a dead body by the girl I like in the near future.</i>

47
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:02,560
<i>And when the time comes,</i>

48
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:06,760
<i>I'll feel quite happy.</i>

49
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:13,320
<i>[One Month Ago]</i>

50
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:17,520
I've got my appetite back! I'm totally recovered.

51
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,920
Oh!

52
00:03:26,830 --> 00:03:29,880
- Are you okay?
- It's no big deal!

53
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:33,190
- Junko, have you started using Instagram?
- No.

54
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:36,670
I was going to send it to Masashi. He caught the flu from me

55
00:03:36,670 --> 00:03:40,020
and he's off sick from work. I thought this would cheer him up.

56
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:43,520
Did you guys do anything to infect him with the flu?

57
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:46,450
It's probably because we slept in the same room.

58
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:50,170
Yuri-yuri and I had the flu.

59
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:52,700
And he insisted on sleeping in the same room.

60
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,890
Maybe guys in their 30s

61
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:59,120
start to sense their paternal instincts.

62
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:02,530
What an idiot

63
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:05,410
<i>he is.</i>

64
00:04:07,590 --> 00:04:09,530
<i>[41.2 Celsius Degree]</i>

65
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,770
How is Yuri-hei doing now?

66
00:04:20,770 --> 00:04:24,030
He's young! He's recovered a long time ago.

67
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:28,020
He got permission from the doctor to return to school tomorrow.

68
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:31,820
Oh, Miwa! No more weird pranks, okay?

69
00:04:31,820 --> 00:04:33,710
Pranks?

70
00:04:33,710 --> 00:04:39,200
Miwa made Yuri-yuri confess to me as a part of her penalty game.

71
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:42,520
I already apologized to you for that.

72
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:45,520
How did he confess to you?

73
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:50,880
He was sort of acting like a chivalrous prince.

74
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:53,770
<i>Watch out for the cars.</i>

75
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:57,610
<i>You're dressing so light again.</i>

76
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:00,110
<i>There's some on your face.</i>

77
00:05:00,110 --> 00:05:05,210
So sweet! Just like the character in a historical dating game, "I will protect you!"

78
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:08,790
He's just like Nobunaga Oda.

79
00:05:08,790 --> 00:05:11,780
His behaviors seriously confused me.

80
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:15,490
<i>Can I have a reward, too?</i>

81
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:19,090
He was shockingly a good actor.

82
00:05:19,090 --> 00:05:21,640
Did you really think he was acting?

83
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:23,750
Mon!

84
00:05:24,690 --> 00:05:27,770
Could you pass me that?

85
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:32,980
Anyway, I am painfully aware of Yuri-yuri's love for me.

86
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:34,060
What?

87
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:38,880
I've never had a student with complete trust in me before.

88
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:43,210
It's so-called, the love between a teacher and student. It's so precious!

89
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:48,530
- Jun...
- Maybe this job is my calling!

90
00:05:48,530 --> 00:05:52,080
If I stand out, maybe I could be a famous teacher!

91
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,580
When will I do it?

92
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:56,580
Now is the time. Now. Now.

93
00:05:56,580 --> 00:05:59,060
Did I sound like him, or not?

94
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:01,390
<i>[Minami High School]</i>

95
00:06:01,390 --> 00:06:03,680
<i>Let's get going.</i>

96
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,430
You're so gross!

97
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:08,770
- What are you doing? Oh!
- It's fine!

98
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:11,360
Kyo!

99
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,990
- Congrats on beating the flu!
- Kyo.

100
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:16,860
Have you totally healed?

101
00:06:18,340 --> 00:06:19,540
He is totally fine now.

102
00:06:19,540 --> 00:06:23,130
- I want some, too. Why not?
- No way.

103
00:06:25,690 --> 00:06:30,890
<i>[Yuka: Submit the divorce paper as soon as possible.]
[Kazuma: I submitted it to the ward office this morning.]</i>

104
00:06:32,580 --> 00:06:34,360
<i>- Don't do that.
- Why not?</i>

105
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,960
- Don't eat it.
- Stop it.

106
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,540
That was close!

107
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:41,030
You're so stingy! What a jerk.

108
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:44,350
<i>Hey. Sorry for the penalty game.</i>

109
00:06:44,350 --> 00:06:48,100
<i>I'm sending you this as an apology. Use it wisely!</i>

110
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:51,030
<i>[Junko in a bikini when she was in her 20's]</i>

111
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:07,010
What's that? A protection amulet?

112
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:09,400
Is this some kind of punishment?

113
00:07:10,770 --> 00:07:13,480
- Show us!
- Shot it to us.

114
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,270
Is that Harumi?

115
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:31,950
On Halloween?

116
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:37,380
It cheers me up.

117
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,450
I see.

118
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:45,180
You're working on some difficult stuff.

119
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:49,670
You're probably the first student ever to study in this library.

120
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:51,630
Are you making fun of me?

121
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:56,120
I'm not. I'm genuinely impressed.

122
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:59,960
But Harumi's always been good at tutoring people.

123
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:03,910
<i>Yamashita is the only person...</i>

124
00:08:03,910 --> 00:08:07,030
<i>who's ever told me he likes me.</i>

125
00:08:08,370 --> 00:08:12,090
Well, as your homeroom teacher,

126
00:08:12,090 --> 00:08:14,180
you can always ask me for anything.

127
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:17,230
Here. Have some food.

128
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,570
Thanks.

129
00:08:42,170 --> 00:08:45,430
It cheers him up, huh?

130
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:07,060
<i>[A Story to Read When You First Fall in Love]</i>

131
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:12,230
<i>[Episode 5]</i>

132
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,150
Here.

133
00:09:23,150 --> 00:09:24,550
<i>[Mika Eto, 60 points]</i>

134
00:09:26,890 --> 00:09:28,820
What?
<i>[Kyohei Yuri, 72 points]</i>

135
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:31,680
Kyo, you got a higher score than me!

136
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:37,130
You let your feelings guide you when answering modern literature questions, right?

137
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:38,350
I suppose.

138
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:42,740
I'm so jealous... I hate modern literature.

139
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:47,130
But that's actually why you got this wrong.

140
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:52,350
For the University of Tokyo's modern literature exams,

141
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:56,760
"Describe the meaning of the underlined word."

142
00:09:56,760 --> 00:10:01,520
Or "What was the purpose of using the particular word."

143
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:04,540
Those are the only questions that will be on the exam.

144
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:07,290
You should be able to understand the real intention of the author

145
00:10:07,290 --> 00:10:09,210
and write that down as it is.

146
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:12,190
In my opinion, that's how I felt.

147
00:10:12,190 --> 00:10:15,070
It's not asking your opinion.

148
00:10:15,070 --> 00:10:17,040
In modern literature,

149
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:20,380
your opinions are irrelevant.

150
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:22,360
Just figure out the author's subjective point of view,

151
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:24,140
and use that as your answer.

152
00:10:24,140 --> 00:10:26,330
But that's so boring!

153
00:10:26,330 --> 00:10:29,430
Is it because you can't share your own opinion?

154
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,960
First, you must understand

155
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,360
the author's feelings accurately

156
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:38,080
without having any preconceptions, only then you can share your opinions.

157
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,940
Expressing your feelings unilaterally,

158
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:42,840
is nothing but an imposition of your opinions on others, right?

159
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,760
It's just like human relationships.

160
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:48,320
If you learn to think like that,

161
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,610
you'll be able to answer it correctly.

162
00:10:50,610 --> 00:10:52,980
You can't just memorize everything when it comes to modern literature.

163
00:10:52,980 --> 00:10:56,670
It's best to review past questions or take some mock exams.

164
00:10:56,670 --> 00:10:58,580
With that said...

165
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:03,110
<i>[The First Nationwide Standardized Mock Exam]</i>

166
00:11:04,170 --> 00:11:05,860
A mock exam?

167
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,030
Don't focus on the results.

168
00:11:08,030 --> 00:11:11,350
I want you to get used to taking the exam.

169
00:11:11,350 --> 00:11:14,050
For the 12th graders who would pass straight out of high school,

170
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:17,640
it's common to get "Grade E" in autumn.
<i>(T/N: The chances of passing is less than 20%)</i>

171
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:19,400
As for now, let's just keep on trying.

172
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,510
Gain more experience, okay?

173
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:28,260
<i>But his math skills still aren't up to par...</i>

174
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:32,970
<i>I studied humanities, so math isn't my strong suit.</i>

175
00:11:32,970 --> 00:11:34,690
<i>I should ask someone to teach him</i>

176
00:11:34,690 --> 00:11:38,790
<i>the basics before the mock exam.</i>

177
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:47,270
Yes. Okay. We'll submit the proposal by Friday.

178
00:11:47,270 --> 00:11:49,300
Okay. Thank you.

179
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:52,820
Okay. Excuse me.

180
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:54,340
Mr. Yakumo,

181
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:56,970
Mr. Imai from Russia wants to inquire about the trade deal?

182
00:11:56,970 --> 00:11:58,680
Okay. I'll give him a call later.

183
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:02,370
The work piled up when you were gone. It's brutal.

184
00:12:02,370 --> 00:12:04,030
Yeah.

185
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:07,740
<i>[Incoming Call: Junko Harumi]</i>

186
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:15,090
Hello? Yes, thank you for calling.

187
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:18,250
Yes, I'm feeling much better.

188
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:21,100
Yes. Now?

189
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:24,120
Well, tonight...

190
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:27,870
I... happen to be free.

191
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:30,020
I'll call you back later.

192
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:38,710
I hope everything goes well.

193
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,560
She's here!

194
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:56,800
Hey.

195
00:12:59,090 --> 00:13:01,510
Why did you want to see me all of a sudden?

196
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:04,770
I'm so glad you got over the flu.

197
00:13:04,770 --> 00:13:06,150
Sorry for the sudden visit.

198
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:09,800
It's fine. It's a bit of a mess, but come in.

199
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,240
Hello there.

200
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,830
Oh, hello.

201
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:20,690
Come on in.

202
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:23,570
<i>[The University of Tokyo, Science Major Study Guide]</i>

203
00:13:23,570 --> 00:13:27,580
Wow, I knew your place would be spacious!

204
00:13:27,580 --> 00:13:31,750
Hold on. Even if you ask me how to conquer the exam for science majors,

205
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:34,760
I haven't studied in almost ten years.

206
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:38,990
I know that. I thought it'd be nice

207
00:13:38,990 --> 00:13:44,220
to have a senior or a tutor nearby whenever he has questions.

208
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:50,180
<i>You like Harumi, don't you?</i>

209
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:53,310
<i>It's obvious, right?</i>

210
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:57,810
He's taking his first mock exam soon.

211
00:13:57,810 --> 00:14:01,500
So I hope you could teach him how to prepare

212
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:04,980
based on your experience from taking the science exam.

213
00:14:04,980 --> 00:14:07,380
Oh! What do we have here?

214
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:08,700
<i>[The University of Tokyo Study Guide: Mathematics]</i>

215
00:14:09,590 --> 00:14:13,460
I see you kept your study guide.

216
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:15,290
Yurie!

217
00:14:18,970 --> 00:14:22,560
As I thought, this covers more than just basic math.

218
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:26,620
Oh well. We'll just have to go over them one by one.

219
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:28,430
Starting with...

220
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:32,040
That's why you've failed the college exam.

221
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:35,970
Listen, the college exam is like getting a job.

222
00:14:35,970 --> 00:14:39,450
You can't study random topics aimlessly.

223
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:45,480
Look at the past exams. The questions are the university's...

224
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,640
Message.

225
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:53,680
Look at the size of the book. Do you know what they're looking for?

226
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:57,710
They don't want serious people that crumble under pressure.

227
00:14:57,710 --> 00:15:04,030
They only accept the most efficient, adaptable, flexible, and quick-thinking students in Japan.

228
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:07,810
I can't tutoring you.

229
00:15:08,690 --> 00:15:10,250
But...

230
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:15,300
I can teach you how I studied.

231
00:15:16,140 --> 00:15:18,550
First, don't study all night.

232
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:21,530
Studying long hours is ineffective.

233
00:15:21,530 --> 00:15:24,630
Take regular breaks.

234
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:30,250
And start getting up early, so you won't be tired during the exam.

235
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:33,450
You don't even know such basics for a prep student?

236
00:15:33,450 --> 00:15:37,620
I was aware, but I wasn't enforcing him.

237
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:40,260
What else...?

238
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:44,920
Right. I used a sketchbook for my math notes.

239
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:46,160
A sketchbook?

240
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:51,730
Right. The answer sheet for the second exam won't have any lines on them.

241
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:55,440
The bigger space, the better you can think.

242
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:58,630
I think I still have it somewhere.

243
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:02,650
Here it is.

244
00:16:06,490 --> 00:16:08,380
<i>[Sketchbook]</i>

245
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:12,720
You want to

246
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:15,700
change your life with the exam, don't you?

247
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:19,430
Then don't study randomly.

248
00:16:19,430 --> 00:16:22,490
Study more efficiently than you ever have before!

249
00:16:24,010 --> 00:16:25,660
Yes, Sir.

250
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,430
Sorry.

251
